                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115C96/29</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Collector <persName type="from">Cobb</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-13T03:00:00-07:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 13, 1916, 3 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Train with bodies reached El Paso without mishap at 2.15 this morning, guarded by
                    20 to 25 soldiers and about 10 Americans armed by permission of Mexican
                    authorities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cobb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
